1
00:01:35,041 --> 00:01:36,321
This person loves to overthink things

2
00:01:36,361 --> 00:01:37,441
about things that don't matter.

3
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:39,921
I suggest you cut ties with him soon.

4
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:41,560
Or you'll end up just as pointless.

5
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:43,121
Hey, watch what you say.

6
00:01:43,161 --> 00:01:44,601
Wen Cheng is my friend too.

7
00:01:44,641 --> 00:01:45,361
And I understand him.

8
00:01:45,401 --> 00:01:46,561
The feeling when your shaobing gets stolen.

9
00:01:47,841 --> 00:01:50,281
Why do you all love shaobing so much?

10
00:01:50,321 --> 00:01:51,801
Hey, stop, stop, stop.

11
00:01:52,561 --> 00:01:54,201
Let's handle things one at a time.

12
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:55,641
Wen Cheng.

13
00:01:55,681 --> 00:01:56,921
What's going on with the show?

14
00:01:58,841 --> 00:02:00,881
The producer asked me to find guests.

15
00:02:00,921 --> 00:02:01,841
So I recommended you.

16
00:02:01,881 --> 00:02:04,241
You're way above Su Wen's league.

17
00:02:04,641 --> 00:02:06,201
You're going on his show?

18
00:02:06,241 --> 00:02:07,321
No way.

19
00:02:07,361 --> 00:02:09,841
I bet you'll never go on his show.

20
00:02:09,881 --> 00:02:10,521
How about this—

21
00:02:10,561 --> 00:02:11,401
I'll do it.

22
00:02:11,441 --> 00:02:13,801
I'll share my years of relationship experience.

23
00:02:13,841 --> 00:02:15,721
And clear my name while I'm at it.

24
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:17,521
Maybe even confess my feelings.

25
00:02:21,841 --> 00:02:22,681
I'm in.

26
00:02:28,201 --> 00:02:29,361
Then I'll go next time.

27
00:02:34,601 --> 00:02:35,561
What's going on?

28
00:02:35,601 --> 00:02:36,281
We're filming live.

29
00:02:36,321 --> 00:02:37,561
Go back, hurry!

30
00:02:37,841 --> 00:02:39,041
Come on, get ready.

31
00:02:39,081 --> 00:02:40,201
Live in five seconds.

32
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,240
Five.

33
00:02:41,521 --> 00:02:41,921
Four.

34
00:02:42,441 --> 00:02:42,881
Three.

35
00:02:43,281 --> 00:02:43,801
Two.

36
00:02:44,241 --> 00:02:45,401
I'm your host, Wen Cheng.

37
00:02:45,441 --> 00:02:47,761
Today we have a very special guest.

38
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:48,761
Let's give a warm welcome to

39
00:02:48,801 --> 00:02:50,121
Jiang Anlan.

40
00:02:50,321 --> 00:02:51,041
Hello, everyone.

41
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:56,000
Jiang Anlan is a top choice for many.

42
00:02:56,041 --> 00:02:57,361
I'm sure you're all curious

43
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,000
how such a cool, handsome guy

44
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:00,681
acts when he's in love.

45
00:03:01,561 --> 00:03:02,761
Just like this, in front of you.

46
00:03:04,001 --> 00:03:05,321
No different from anyone else.

47
00:03:06,001 --> 00:03:07,761
You're not the one I love.

48
00:03:07,801 --> 00:03:08,961
So you can't feel it.

49
00:03:09,361 --> 00:03:11,681
I bet many people want to know too.

50
00:03:11,721 --> 00:03:13,281
Would you share with us

51
00:03:13,321 --> 00:03:15,361
how you treat the woman you love?

52
00:03:16,521 --> 00:03:19,281
My whole world revolves around her.

53
00:03:20,001 --> 00:03:21,361
What's with this guy?

54
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:22,961
Even using his friends now.

55
00:03:23,841 --> 00:03:24,561
He's just

56
00:03:24,601 --> 00:03:26,281
sharing his own opinion.

57
00:03:26,321 --> 00:03:27,641
Hasn't had the chance yet.

58
00:03:27,681 --> 00:03:29,481
He goes on the show every week.

59
00:03:31,321 --> 00:03:32,201
Who are you talking about?

60
00:03:33,961 --> 00:03:34,801
Wen Cheng.

61
00:03:35,881 --> 00:03:36,921
I'm talking about Jiang Anlan.

62
00:03:38,401 --> 00:03:39,041
It's fine.

63
00:03:39,081 --> 00:03:40,561
In some people's eyes,

64
00:03:40,601 --> 00:03:41,521
there's only Wen Cheng.

65
00:03:42,721 --> 00:03:44,121
So if I look at your husband—

66
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:49,001
That sounds so abstract.

67
00:03:49,041 --> 00:03:51,161
Do you spend all day circling around her?

68
00:03:52,241 --> 00:03:53,361
If I could,

69
00:03:53,401 --> 00:03:54,401
I'd honestly want to.

70
00:03:55,921 --> 00:03:56,641
Let me ask you this—

71
00:03:57,401 --> 00:03:58,121
When you like someone,

72
00:03:58,161 --> 00:03:59,681
what do you actually do?

73
00:04:01,121 --> 00:04:03,121
I set up an inescapable net around her.

74
00:04:03,641 --> 00:04:05,561
No other man crosses the line.

75
00:04:07,881 --> 00:04:09,281
Isn't that a bit possessive?

76
00:04:09,601 --> 00:04:10,761
Not when I do it.

77
00:04:12,081 --> 00:04:14,081
You seem really confident in yourself.

78
00:04:14,961 --> 00:04:16,921
I'm confident in our love.

79
00:04:17,681 --> 00:04:19,841
Isn't love supposed to be

80
00:04:19,881 --> 00:04:21,201
the most unreliable thing in the world?

81
00:04:22,561 --> 00:04:23,721
I'm the reliable one.

82
00:04:24,801 --> 00:04:26,321
That's an amazing answer.

83
00:04:30,481 --> 00:04:32,361
Since he's already here to visit,

84
00:04:32,401 --> 00:04:33,361
how about

85
00:04:33,401 --> 00:04:34,001
later on,

86
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:35,521
you both go on the show together?

87
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,640
Who joins a show halfway through?

88
00:04:38,561 --> 00:04:40,721
We can't always stick to tradition.

89
00:04:40,761 --> 00:04:42,361
We need to innovate.

90
00:04:42,401 --> 00:04:43,281
Right?

91
00:04:43,321 --> 00:04:44,681
The path's always looked like this.

92
00:04:44,721 --> 00:04:45,921
There's a reason for that.

93
00:04:47,161 --> 00:04:48,281
Su Wen isn't exactly

94
00:04:48,321 --> 00:04:49,881
an unknown figure.

95
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,161
When people see him,

96
00:04:51,201 --> 00:04:52,441
they get excited.

97
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:54,721
Who cares about the little details?

98
00:04:55,601 --> 00:04:57,081
No wonder you're the company's

99
00:04:57,121 --> 00:04:58,721
famous producer.

100
00:04:59,041 --> 00:05:00,801
You know how to adapt.

101
00:05:04,001 --> 00:05:04,801
So,

102
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,080
you two will go on the show together later.

103
00:05:07,721 --> 00:05:08,481
Boss Jiang,

104
00:05:08,521 --> 00:05:09,361
is that okay with you?

105
00:05:17,401 --> 00:05:18,561
A mysterious guest just appeared here.

106
00:05:18,601 --> 00:05:20,281
A very mysterious guest.

107
00:05:20,321 --> 00:05:21,961
Let’s give a warm welcome

108
00:05:22,001 --> 00:05:23,361
to photographer Su Wen.

109
00:05:27,201 --> 00:05:29,441
Su Wen is openly declaring war, huh?

110
00:05:33,081 --> 00:05:34,761
Su Wen is a master in romance.

111
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:36,041
The kind people love to hate.

112
00:05:36,561 --> 00:05:38,521
He’s joining our show today

113
00:05:38,561 --> 00:05:40,001
to share with us

114
00:05:40,041 --> 00:05:41,321
his tips for winning a girl’s heart.

115
00:05:41,721 --> 00:05:42,281
I don’t want to.

116
00:05:42,641 --> 00:05:43,081
Ah.

117
00:05:44,201 --> 00:05:45,481
I want to talk about it too.

118
00:05:45,521 --> 00:05:46,561
When I fall in love,

119
00:05:46,601 --> 00:05:47,201
I

120
00:05:47,241 --> 00:05:48,041
wonder what I’ll be like.

121
00:05:49,681 --> 00:05:51,361
We really don’t want to know.

122
00:05:52,241 --> 00:05:53,841
I only have eyes for that person.

123
00:05:54,361 --> 00:05:56,361
I don’t care about anyone else.

124
00:05:56,401 --> 00:05:57,841
Just want to stay by her side.

125
00:05:58,681 --> 00:06:01,601
Then you must be blind all year round.

126
00:06:01,641 --> 00:06:03,161
And most of your income

127
00:06:03,201 --> 00:06:04,601
is spent on travel expenses.

128
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:08,161
That was the old me you’re talking about.

129
00:06:08,921 --> 00:06:11,241
Let the past die with yesterday;

130
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,640
let the future be born with tomorrow.

131
00:06:14,921 --> 00:06:16,641
So, what will the new Su Wen be like?

132
00:06:16,681 --> 00:06:17,641
What will he look like?

133
00:06:18,441 --> 00:06:19,121
From now on,

134
00:06:19,161 --> 00:06:20,441
I’ll only care about one person.

135
00:06:21,801 --> 00:06:23,081
That’s for the future.

136
00:06:23,121 --> 00:06:24,681
Why talk about it now?

137
00:06:25,241 --> 00:06:27,161
True love can’t be forced.

138
00:06:27,601 --> 00:06:29,241
We have to keep trying

139
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:31,320
to find the one who suits us best.

140
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:33,521
But usually not three at once.

141
00:06:35,201 --> 00:06:37,441
That’s usually just a rumor.

142
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,640
I just try three in a row.

143
00:06:40,401 --> 00:06:42,321
We only live to eighty.

144
00:06:42,361 --> 00:06:43,961
How long will you let morals tie you down?

145
00:06:45,561 --> 00:06:46,641
It’s not about moral coercion.

146
00:06:46,681 --> 00:06:48,641
It’s about respecting relationships.

147
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:51,880
Don’t let past failures

148
00:06:51,921 --> 00:06:53,361
make you give up future happiness.

149
00:06:53,921 --> 00:06:55,161
Do you respect yourself?

150
00:06:56,761 --> 00:06:58,441
Past relationships aren’t failures.

151
00:06:58,481 --> 00:07:00,521
They’re memories, nutrients for growth.

152
00:07:01,481 --> 00:07:02,401
Nutrients?

153
00:07:02,441 --> 00:07:04,121
What are nutrients anyway?

154
00:07:04,161 --> 00:07:05,721
Nutrients come from what’s dead.

155
00:07:06,081 --> 00:07:07,401
Once it’s dead, it won’t come back.

156
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:08,681
What’s alive

157
00:07:08,721 --> 00:07:10,161
is what we should care about most.

158
00:07:11,481 --> 00:07:13,161
I’ve only been in love once.

159
00:07:13,681 --> 00:07:15,681
I plan for it to be my only one.

160
00:07:15,721 --> 00:07:16,601
This topic

161
00:07:16,641 --> 00:07:17,801
I’ll leave it to you all.

162
00:07:20,241 --> 00:07:22,041
I’ve decided to follow my boss’s lead.

163
00:07:22,361 --> 00:07:23,681
And lately I’ve noticed

164
00:07:23,721 --> 00:07:25,001
my taste is becoming more like my boss’s.

165
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:25,921
More and more alike.

166
00:07:28,521 --> 00:07:29,521
Because of my situation,

167
00:07:29,561 --> 00:07:31,681
there’s been a lot of gossip lately.

168
00:07:31,721 --> 00:07:33,001
I don’t want to clarify anything.

169
00:07:33,041 --> 00:07:35,161
I believe truth speaks for itself.

170
00:07:35,561 --> 00:07:37,321
I’m honored to be on this show today.

171
00:07:37,361 --> 00:07:39,081
I want to share my views on love.

172
00:07:39,641 --> 00:07:41,521
I think this show is great.

173
00:07:41,561 --> 00:07:42,521
It’s a good chance to clear up

174
00:07:42,561 --> 00:07:43,681
everyone’s misunderstandings about me.

175
00:07:45,401 --> 00:07:46,241
Who cares?

176
00:07:48,641 --> 00:07:50,121
I’m holding an exhibition soon.

177
00:07:50,161 --> 00:07:51,721
Through a woman I care about,

178
00:07:51,761 --> 00:07:53,441
I’ve found my true self again.

179
00:07:59,961 --> 00:08:00,521
Boss.

180
00:08:02,121 --> 00:08:02,761
Coffee.

181
00:08:09,561 --> 00:08:11,441
How much longer is our contract with Su Wen?

182
00:08:12,241 --> 00:08:12,881
A long time.

183
00:08:13,401 --> 00:08:14,161
Why?

184
00:08:14,881 --> 00:08:17,001
Because you thought you had great taste.

185
00:08:17,521 --> 00:08:18,241
Su Wen.

186
00:08:18,441 --> 00:08:19,321
He’s got a bright future.

187
00:08:22,041 --> 00:08:23,441
How much to break the contract?

188
00:08:24,201 --> 00:08:24,761
Terminate the contract?

189
00:08:25,201 --> 00:08:25,801
Trust me,

190
00:08:26,521 --> 00:08:28,121
you won’t spend that much on Su Wen.

191
00:08:42,321 --> 00:08:43,161
What are you doing?

192
00:08:43,801 --> 00:08:45,481
Su Wen must want to photograph you.

193
00:08:45,521 --> 00:08:46,881
I’d better be careful.

194
00:08:47,961 --> 00:08:49,721
It’s too dark, he can’t get a clear shot.

195
00:08:49,761 --> 00:08:50,601
He’s not a paparazzo.

196
00:08:50,961 --> 00:08:52,241
Doesn’t he love to capture

197
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:53,521
real moments?

198
00:08:53,761 --> 00:08:55,601
I can’t let him see your beauty.

199
00:08:56,321 --> 00:08:58,161
Is that possessiveness talking,

200
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,880
or do you really mean it?

201
00:08:59,921 --> 00:09:00,801
Both.

202
00:09:01,281 --> 00:09:03,121
All my possessiveness

203
00:09:03,161 --> 00:09:05,521
is always based on sincerity.

204
00:09:09,521 --> 00:09:11,361
It’s just the neighbor’s dog barking.

205
00:09:11,401 --> 00:09:12,721
Why are you so sensitive?

206
00:09:13,001 --> 00:09:14,521
Dogs are sensitive animals.

207
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:16,680
There must be an uninvited guest.

208
00:09:18,281 --> 00:09:19,521
What if it’s barking at you?

209
00:09:19,801 --> 00:09:20,961
No way.

210
00:09:21,001 --> 00:09:22,561
Unless Su Wen is playing the dog.

211
00:09:24,441 --> 00:09:25,921
Alright, you go now.

212
00:09:26,121 --> 00:09:26,881
I’m heading back.

213
00:09:27,241 --> 00:09:28,561
No, I have to walk you in.

214
00:09:30,121 --> 00:09:31,641
Is Su Wen at my place?

215
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,360
Maybe.

216
00:09:32,401 --> 00:09:33,521
I need to check for you.

217
00:09:34,961 --> 00:09:37,041
Why do I feel you have other motives?

218
00:09:39,441 --> 00:09:40,201
I’m leaving.

219
00:09:52,321 --> 00:09:53,521
Sis, I’m back.

220
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,320
You’re back.

221
00:09:54,361 --> 00:09:55,761
Hey, let me tell you what I bought today—

222
00:09:57,601 --> 00:09:59,001
Master, why are you here?

223
00:09:59,321 --> 00:10:00,441
You didn’t even say anything.

224
00:10:00,481 --> 00:10:01,161
Something came up.

225
00:10:02,321 --> 00:10:03,681
Weren’t you going to the bar?

226
00:10:04,881 --> 00:10:06,241
Li Xiaoya ditched me.

227
00:10:06,281 --> 00:10:07,161
Stood me up.

228
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:09,761
Hi, Xinran.

229
00:10:11,401 --> 00:10:13,161
You two just treat me like I’m invisible.

230
00:10:13,201 --> 00:10:14,201
Go ahead, keep going.

231
00:10:14,241 --> 00:10:15,601
Wish you both happiness.

232
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,280
Sit.

233
00:10:25,121 --> 00:10:26,521
Want some water? I’ll get you some.

234
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,200
I’m not thirsty.

235
00:10:28,921 --> 00:10:29,521
Are you hungry?

236
00:10:30,081 --> 00:10:31,041
I’ll cook for you.

237
00:10:31,081 --> 00:10:31,721
Fried rice.

238
00:10:31,761 --> 00:10:32,361
Sound good?

239
00:10:33,481 --> 00:10:34,481
Anything you make is fine.

240
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,280
Close the door.

241
00:10:59,761 --> 00:11:00,441
Su Wen can’t take photos,

242
00:11:00,481 --> 00:11:01,601
but you can, right?

243
00:11:02,401 --> 00:11:02,761
That’s right.

244
00:11:03,241 --> 00:11:05,561
That’s one rule for them,

245
00:11:05,601 --> 00:11:06,801
another for us.

246
00:11:08,241 --> 00:11:09,641
So you’re saying you’re the official?

247
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,200
Yeah.

248
00:11:10,601 --> 00:11:12,641
Su Wen is just a regular person.

249
00:11:23,441 --> 00:11:24,281
Looks pretty good, right?

250
00:11:27,481 --> 00:11:28,641
This is

251
00:11:28,680 --> 00:11:29,920
soy sauce fried rice.

252
00:11:31,801 --> 00:11:32,761
It's not burnt.

253
00:11:32,801 --> 00:11:33,641
Don't get me wrong.

254
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,440
I just added a bit too much soy sauce.

255
00:11:35,481 --> 00:11:36,641
Our soy sauce isn't salty.

256
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:37,360
Really.

257
00:11:38,921 --> 00:11:40,801
This probably isn't the soy sauce's fault.

258
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:43,001
Try it first.

259
00:11:43,241 --> 00:11:44,281
Maybe it'll taste good.

260
00:12:00,521 --> 00:12:01,841
Just like I imagined.

261
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:02,920
Is it good?

262
00:12:02,961 --> 00:12:03,321
It's good.

263
00:12:06,441 --> 00:12:06,921
You try it.

264
00:12:16,161 --> 00:12:16,761
Let's order takeout.

265
00:12:16,801 --> 00:12:17,121
Okay.

266
00:12:19,841 --> 00:12:20,521
Sorry.

267
00:12:20,881 --> 00:12:21,561
It's fine.

268
00:12:21,841 --> 00:12:23,081
I'm really good at cooking.

269
00:12:23,121 --> 00:12:23,641
From now on,

270
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:24,440
I'll do the cooking.

271
00:12:24,481 --> 00:12:25,441
You just need to eat.

272
00:12:25,881 --> 00:12:26,881
Do you like Northeastern cuisine?

273
00:12:26,921 --> 00:12:27,601
I'm fine with it.

274
00:12:34,521 --> 00:12:35,241
Hello?

275
00:12:35,281 --> 00:12:35,881
This is Yao Xinran.

276
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:37,041
Who are you looking for?

277
00:12:37,081 --> 00:12:38,201
Hi, I'm Su Wen.

278
00:12:38,481 --> 00:12:40,481
I want to join Planner Yao's art exchange project.

279
00:12:40,521 --> 00:12:41,321
As a photography instructor.

280
00:12:41,641 --> 00:12:42,281
Great, great.

281
00:12:42,841 --> 00:12:43,641
I can arrange that.

282
00:12:44,081 --> 00:12:45,001
Don't worry.

283
00:12:45,041 --> 00:12:46,041
It's an honor to work with you.

284
00:12:46,081 --> 00:12:47,081
It's truly our privilege.

285
00:12:49,001 --> 00:12:49,921
